Here we go… many are asking what’s going on, where have you been? Exhibit “A”, knee. Ready to share now that have some answers. Key point, I’ll be just fine, have several doctors on board & sorting out this extremely frustrating ordeal. I’ll be taking more breaks, even at City Hall before a live shot, shoes in this pix are cushy & one level that’s not high. 
  May 22nd, after a lot of research, had hyaluronic acid injection in my left knee for chronic pain. Doctors now say I had an extreme reaction to the shot. What followed has been an awful journey..pain, redness, swelling, nasty bruising, stiffness, could not touch the knee. I had no relief after oral steroids, cortisone shot, antibiotics, over the counter & prescription anti inflammatory meds. Blood work, MRI & sonogram showed nothing unusual. Recently things finally eased after getting a muscular steroid shot. All of this was a curve ball, has been mentally & physically agonizing. Final diagnoses, panniculitis..I know.. weird word, inflammation of deep fatty tissue. Muscle & skin are also very angry. Have a plan in place now but the hardest part, it will take time to resolve 😡 So for the next few months, walking like a sloth 😂 not overdoing it, no heels 🤦🏽‍♀️ listening to my body. I’m sharing, hoping to urge others to…even though it’s tough & exhausting…ask a million questions, be your own advocate & stay the course even when you’re overwhelmed 💃🏽
